@startuml
skin rose
title GDP Message - **UPDATE INVALID / EXPIRED** Flow

queue "GDP Event Hub" as Queue
participant "GDP Message Consumer" as Consumer
database "Redis\n(Idempotency Key Store)" as REDIS
participant "SP Creditore" as SPC
database "SRTP" as SRTP
participant "SP Debitore" as SPD

Queue -> Consumer: **GDP Message**
note left
  **Operation = UPDATE**
  **Status = INVALID** or **EXPIRED**
end note

activate Consumer

Consumer -> REDIS: **Check Idempotency-Key**
activate REDIS

alt **Idempotency-Key already present**
  REDIS --> Consumer: **Key found**
  deactivate REDIS
  Consumer -> Consumer: **Discard duplicated message**
  note right
    Message already processed
    or already in processing
  end note

else **Idempotency-Key not present**
  REDIS --> Consumer: **Key not found**
  Consumer -> REDIS: **Save Idempotency-Key**
  REDIS --> Consumer: **Key saved**
  deactivate REDIS

  Consumer -> SPC: **Process UPDATE INVALID / EXPIRED**
  activate SPC

  SPC -> SRTP: **findRtpByCompositeKey**
  activate SRTP

  alt **RTP exists**
    SRTP --> SPC: **RTP**
    deactivate SRTP

    note right
      Valid statuses for cancellation:
      - CREATED
      - SENT
      - ACCEPTED
      - USER_ACCEPTED

      ---
      Cancellation request initiated
    end note

    alt **Status is valid**
      SPC -> SPD: **POST /sepa-request-to-pay-requests/{id}/cancellation-requests**
      note right: Send **cancellation request** to SP Debtor
      activate SPD

      alt **Async flow EPC**
        SPD --> SPC: **OK empty Body**
        SPC -> SPC: **Set RTP status to RFC_SENT**
        SPC -> SRTP: **Save RTP with RFC_SENT status**
        activate SRTP
        SRTP --> SPC: **Saved RTP**
        deactivate SRTP

      else **Sync flow EPC**
        SPD --> SPC: **OK payload**
        SPC -> SPC: **Set RTP status to CANCELLED**
        SPC -> SRTP: **Save RTP with CANCELLED status**
        activate SRTP
        SRTP --> SPC: **Saved RTP**
        deactivate SRTP

      else **Error Sync Response**
        SPD --> SPC: **Error response (e.g., 4xx, 5xx)**
        SPC -> SPC: **Set RTP status to ERROR_CANCEL**
        SPC -> SRTP: **Save RTP with ERROR_CANCEL status**
        activate SRTP
        SRTP --> SPC: **Saved RTP**
        deactivate SRTP
      end

      deactivate SPD
      SPC --> Consumer: **Outcome processed**

    else **Invalid RTP status for cancellation**
      SPC --> Consumer: **Error – Invalid RTP status**
      note right: RTP is already in a final state (e.g., PAID, REJECTED)
    end

  else **RTP not found**
    SRTP --> SPC: **Not found**
    deactivate SRTP
    SPC --> Consumer: **Error – RTP not found**
  end

  deactivate SPC
end

deactivate Consumer
@enduml